Which of the following keys can you select as the primary key in a relational database? Select all that apply.

1 / 1 point

Foreign Key


Composite Key

Correct
Correct! The Composite key is composed of multiple columns to form a unique value in each row of the table, which makes it suitable to be chosen as a primary key.


Alternate key

Correct
Correct! Alternate key has unique values in each row of the table, which makes it suitable to be chosen as a primary key. 


Candidate Key

Correct
Correct! A candidate key has unique values in each row of the table. 